014 Hypo-Meeting}}\n|{{flagathlete|[[Trey Hardee]]|USA}} || 8518 \n|{{flagathlete|[[Katarina Johnson-Thompson]]|GBR}} || 6682\n|-\n|'''[[2015 in athletics (track and field)|2015]]'''<br>&nbsp; {{DetailsLink|2015 Hypo-Meeting}}\n|{{flagathlete|[[Kai Kazmirek]]|GER}} || 8462 \n|{{flagathlete|[[Brianne Theisen-Eaton]]|CAN}} || 6808\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n|'''[[2016 in athletics (track and field)|2016]]'''<br>&nbsp; {{DetailsLink|2016 Hypo-Meeting}}\n|{{flagathlete|[[Damian Warner]]|CAN}} || 8523\n|{{flagathlete|[[Brianne Theisen-Eaton]]|CAN}} || 6765\n|-\n|'''[[2017 in athletics (track and field)|2017]]'''<br>&nbsp; {{DetailsLink|2017 Hypo-Meeting}}\n|{{flagathlete|[[Damian Warner]]|CAN}} || 8591\n|{{flagathlete|[[Nafissatou Thiam]]|BEL}} || 7013\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n|'''[[2018 in athletics (track and field)|2018]]'''<br>&nbsp; {{DetailsLink|2018 Hypo-Meeting}}\n|{{flagathlete|[[Damian Warner]]|CAN}} || 8795\n|{{flagathlete|[[Nafissatou Thiam]]|BEL}} || 6806\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n|'''[[2019 in athletics (track and field)|2019]]'''<br>&nbsp; {{DetailsLink|2019 Hypo-Meeting}}\n|{{flagathlete|[[Damian Warner]]|CAN}} || 8711\n|{{flagathlete|[[Katarina Johnson-Thompson]]|GBR}} || 6813\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*{{Official website|www.meeting-goetzis.at}}\n\n{{Hypo-Meeting}}\n{{IAAF Challenges}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hypo-Meeting}}\n[[Category:Hypo-Meeting| ]]\n[[Category:Vorarlberg]]\n[[Category:Decathlon]]\n[[Category:Annual track and field meetings]]\n[[Category:Recurring sporting events established in 1975]]\n[[Category:International athletics competitions hosted by Austria]]\n[[Category:IAAF Combined Events Challenge]]\n[[Category:1975 establishments in Austria]]\n", "text_old": "The '''Hypo-Meeting''' is an annual [[athletics (sport)|athletics]] competition that takes place in the M\u00f6sle stadium in [[G\u00f6tzis]] in [[Vorarlberg]] ([[Austria]]) held in the spring (late May, early June). In its history, a total of three world records have been set: 1980 and 1982 by [[Daley Thompson]] (8648 and 8730 points), and 2001 by [[Roman \u0160ebrle]] (9026 points)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://meeting-goetzis.at/en/meeting/facts-figures/|title=Facts & Figures Meeting G\u00f6tzis|website=meeting-goetzis.at|language=en|access-date=2018-03-13}}</ref>. \n\nOrganised by the [[International Association of Athletics Federations]] (IAAF), it is one of the athletics meetings that make up the [[IAAF Combined Events Challenge]]. Male and female athletes compete in the [[decathlon]] or [[heptathlon]], respectively, and points scored at the Hypo-Meeting count towards a yearly total for the parent competition.\n\n== History ==\nIn 1972, the Montfort community for athletics (''Leichtathletikgemeinschaft Montfort'') was founded in G\u00f6tzis, Vorarlberg.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vol.at/lg-montfort-ist-geschichte/2498269|title=LG Montfort ist Geschichte|website=vol.at|access-date=2019-06-17}}</ref> A year later, the community offered to hold the Austrian Multi-Discipline Championship which they ultimately did in 1975, superseding the traditional multi-discipline event in Schielleiten.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://meeting-goetzis.at/ueber-uns|website=meeting-goetzis.at|access-date=2019-06-17}}</ref> The first Hypo-Meeting began as a men's only contest in 1975 and a women's competition was added in 1981.\n\nThe meeting has been sponsored by the [[Hypo Landesbank Vorarlberg]] for over 30 years now, hence its name.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://meeting-goetzis.at/sponsoren|website=meeting-goetzis.at|access-date=2019-06-17}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Hypo-Meeting 2015, G\u00f6tzis, \u00d6sterreich.jpg|thumb|2015 Hypo-Meeting]]\n\n==Competition format==\nFollowing the setup of virtually all major combined events competitions, the events programme is split over two days.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:95%;\" width=\"90%\"\n|-\n!colspan=2|Decathlon\n!colspan=